Azure Site Recovery (ASR) is a disaster recovery service that replicates workloads to Azure.

It enables failover and failback during outages.

For example, an application running on-premise can failover to Azure during a disaster.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is business continuity planning.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is protecting critical systems from downtime.

ASR ensures minimal disruption and quick recovery.
